<P>
 Your commentary ("The Uphill Fight of a Downbeat Comedy," TV Times, March 20) 
speaks of former 13th Floor Elevators frontman Roky Erickson (not Rocky) almost 
as if he were dead. ("(He) spent most of the rest of his life in an insane 
asylum ...").Let the Associated Press' Scott Williams and John Larroquette know 
that Roky -- institutionalized or not, at this point -- is alive and was still 
releasing records as recently as 1988. 
</P>
<P>
 Veronica Moore, Los Angeles Hollywood's Big Night 
</P>
<P>
 I would like to thank television news, the media, the newspapers and radio for 
making Oscar night absolutely predictable, with no surprises whatsoever. 
</P>
<P>
 There is so much hype and so much talk for so long before the big night that 
even if you were living in Siberia, you would know who the winners would be. 
</P>
<P>
 Toni Jacobson, Monterey Park 
</P>
<P>
 Whoopi Goldberg deserves an Oscar for her performance as emcee during the 
Academy Awards. She was funny, good-natured and, most importantly, kept the 
show at a good pace. I look forward to seeing her recast next year. 
</P>
<P>
 Amanda Q. Madison, Beverly Hills 
