<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOVIES TO TAPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kevin Thomas 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Withnail & I (Bravo Monday at 5 and 10 p.m.) is Bruce Robinson's sly, 
hilarious 1986 account of two seedy young Londoners (Richard E. Grant, Paul 
McGann) on a country holiday. 
</P>
<P>
 Hidden Agenda (HBO Thursday at 4:15 a.m.), set in Belfast in the the early 
1980s, is a taut 1990 Ken Loach thriller that indicts the shoot-to-kill 
ruthlessness of the British police.With Frances McDormand, Brian Cox. 
</P>
<P>
 The Emigrants (Bravo Thursday at 6 and 11 p.m.). Jan Troell's superb 1971 
account of the migration of Swedish farm families to America in the mid-19th 
Century, stars Max Von Sydow and Liv Ullmann. 
</P>
<P>
 Thelonius Monk: Straight, No Chaser (Bravo Saturday at 5 p.m.) is an 
outstanding, full-scale 1988 documentary by Charlotte Zwerin on the jazz 
innovator. 
</P>
