Frank Sinatra's "Duets" leave you unsatisfied? Bass-master Wasserman's latest 
project ups the ante, as he anchors a series of sparkling threesomes for real 
musical interplay, crossing genres (Primus' Les Claypool with blues-rocker 
Chris Whitley) and generations (Carnie Wilson reunited with her dad, 
Brian).Other participants of note include Elvis Costello, Willie Dixon and Neil 
Young. 
