<P>
By ROBERT LEVINE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * * * Eugenius, "Mary Queen of Scots," Atlantic. The second album from this 
Glasgow band, fronted by ex-Vaseline Eugene Kelly, is an oddly addictive mix of 
Velvet Underground-style distortion and crystal-clear vocals.Muted melodies 
begin beautifully, fill with tension and then explode into bursts of guitar 
feedback with little warning. "Pebble" and "Easter Bunny" are as haunting as 
they are easy to sing along with. 
</P>
