<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS; DEAL OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Presidente Ixtapa, a 400-room resort hotel in Ixtapa, about 130 miles 
northwest of Acapulco, is offering an "off-season" special "Sunbreaks" program 
through July 8. For an all-inclusive price of $130 per night, based on double 
occupancy, two travelers get a standard double room, all meals, all snacks and 
all drinks -- alcoholic and non.Resort facilities include pools, tennis courts, 
kids activities and a variety of classes such as aerobics, language, 
handicrafts and cooking. The package depends on availability and there are no 
blackout dates. The price does not include air fare. For information and 
reservations, call (800) 447-6147. Free for the Asking 
</P>
<P>
 Want to know what's happening in Honolulu, Houston or Hong Kong? A call to the 
convention and visitors' bureau in these cities -- or one of nearly 400 around 
the world -- will produce a fistful of information, including maps, local 
guides, lists of attractions, schedules of events and descriptions of all kinds 
of accommodations and restaurants. So, where do you find the bureaus' telephone 
numbers? In the International Assn. of Convention & Visitor Bureaus' newly 
updated, pocket-sized directory of member bureaus. To get yours, send a 
stamped, self-addressed envelope to Directory, IACVB, P.O. Box 6690 Champaign, 
Ill. 61826. 
</P>
</TEXT>
