<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS; CALIFORNIA CORNER: FESTIVALS, FEASTS & FAIRS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY FRANCES SMITH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 SAN DIEGO -- Spend a day at the bay at the San Diego Crew Classic, Saturday 
and April 10. More than 80 clubs, universities and colleges are represented in 
competitions, 7 a.m.-4 p.m. Saturday; 7 a.m.-3:30 p.m. Sunday at Crown Point 
Shores on Mission Bay.$5, general; free for kids 12 and under. (619) 488-0700. 
</P>
<P>
 OXNARD -- The second Taste of Ventura County, April 15-17, offers foods and 
beverages from about 20 restaurants, plus music and kids' activities, 5-11 p.m. 
Friday; noon-11 p.m. Saturday; 11 a.m.-8 p.m. Sunday. Festivities are at the 
Channel Islands Harbor, 2950 S. Harbor Blvd. $6, general; $3, seniors over 55 
and military; free for kids under 12. (Food/beverages: $1-$6.) (800) 994-4852. 
</P>
<P>
 WALNUT CREEK -- The Civic Park Community Center is aglitter at the Great 
Contra Costa Crystal Fair, 10 a.m.-6 p.m. April 16; 10 a.m.-4 p.m. April 17. 
Featured: crystals, minerals, gems, jewelry. Civic Drive at Broadway. $4, 
general; free for kids under 12. (415) 383-7837. DEVORE -- Sixteenth-Century 
merriment are featured at the 32nd annual Renaissance Pleasure Faire, 
Saturdays-Sundays, April 16-June 5 (and Monday, May 30). 9 a.m.-6 p.m. daily in 
Glen Helen Regional Park, at the northern junction of interstates 15 and 215. 
$16.50, general; $13.50, students, seniors, military; $7.50, kids 5-11; free 
for kids 4 and under. (800) 52-FAIRE. 
</P>
<P>
 HEALDSBURG -- Fine arts and crafts are showcased at Art on the Move, a mobile 
celebration in downtown venues, noon-5 p.m. April 17. $10. Tickets available at 
Center Art Center, Summerhouse Gallery, Toyon Books and Simi Winery. (707) 
431-1814. 
</P>
<P>
 Call listed phone numbers for directions. MARY FRANCES SMITH 
</P>
