JONES CAPTURES MIDGET MAIN IN VENTURA RACEWAY OPENER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DARIN ESPER, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Page Jones of Torrance, the son of two-time Indy 500 winner Parnelli Jones, 
passed pole-sitting Ron Shuman in the first turn and led the rest of the race 
to win the 30-lap USAC midget main event Saturday in the Ventura Raceway season 
opener. 
</P>
<P>
 Jones survived three caution flags and an apparent handling problem to win the 
race.He opened up a quarter-lap lead by the fifth lap before the first caution 
flag came up on Lap 8 when his teammate, Jason Leffler of Long Beach, spun. 
</P>
<P>
 John Cofer of Macdoel, Calif., won the 12-lap midget semi-main event in 
2:09.50. 
</P>
<P>
 In the three-quarter main event, Simi Valley's Scott Hansen, who was the 
fastest qualifier at 13.388, led 11 of 20 laps and notched his second victory 
in three races. 
</P>
<P>
 Hansen led for five laps before giving way to Rick Atkins of Fullerton on Lap 
9, but regained the lead on Lap 13 when Atkins almost spun out through the 
first turn. 
</P>
<P>
 Jeff Gregory of Elk Grove took the three-quarter semi-main in 1:53.91. 
</P>
<P>
 Jay Drake of Val Verde won the first midget heat in 1:43.01, Cary Faab of 
Yorba Linda took the second heat with a 1:45.25 clocking, Tony Stewart of 
Indianapolis won the third heat in 1:43.35, and Sun Valley's Walt Johnson won 
the fourth heat. 
</P>
