<HEADLINE>
<P>
A BALDWIN BROTHERS CRIB SHEET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by the Film Clips staff 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 There were, at last count, four members of that famous Long Island thespian 
family, the Baldwins of Massapequa, active before the cameras of Hollywood. And 
you have to admit it: Sometimes it's tough to tell this set of sexy siblings 
apart. Sure, it's easy to remember that Alec is the one who married Kim 
Basinger. But it was Daniel or William who showed up in "Three of Hearts," the 
romantic comedy about a three-way love affair? Stephen or Daniel who played 
Daryl Hannah's caddish husband in "Attack of the 50-Foot Woman"? Stephen or 
William in "8 Seconds," playing a real-life rodeo star? Herewith, the 
definitive guide to help tell those pesky Baldwins apart. 
</P>
<P>
 Name: Alec Age: 35 Significant other: Wife Kim Basinger, married August, 1993. 
First made an impression: On "Knots Landing," as a randy evangelist. Movie 
breakthrough role: As lovable CIA agent Jack Ryan in "The Hunt for Red 
October." Most recently seen: Imitating Steve McQueen in "The Getaway." Look: 
Leading man handsomeness: killer smile, blue eyes, great physique. Typical 
role: Suave, intelligent, cool leading man with sensitivity and 
self-deprecating sense of humor. Chest hair: Like a gorilla. If he didn't shave 
his neck, his chest hair would grow all the way to his eyebrows. 
Extracurricular activities: Animal rights activism; moral support of Kim's 
trial. Career trajectory: On the rise until "Marrying Man" debacle; playing 
Broadway cost him Jack Ryan franchise; still the biggest star of the four but 
in need of a hit; maybe summer's "The Shadow" will do the trick. * 
</P>
<P>
 Name: Daniel Age: 33 Significant other: Wife Elizabeth; married April, 1990 
First made an impression: As a talkative detective with marital problems on 
cult NBC hit "Homicide: Life on the Street." Movie breakthrough role: Still 
waiting. Most recently seen: In HBO's remake of "Attack of the 50-Foot Woman," 
flailing helplessly in Daryl Hannah's hand. Look: Alec, with jowls. Looks 
chunkier than he is because he lacks a neck. Typical role: Cocky sidekick; 
lowlife philanderer with a bad attitude. Chest hair: Unknown; has yet to doff 
his shirt in a prominent role. Extracurricular activities: Until recently, 
waiting to see if "Homicide" was going to be renewed (it was). Career 
trajectory: Needs to make an impact in a big film or be reduced to being the 
Zeppo of the Baldwin brothers. * 
</P>
<P>
 Name: William Age: 31 Significant other: Most recently linked to Chynne 
Philips. First made an impression: In "Flatliners," as Kevorkian manque with a 
conscience. Movie breakthrough role: As sexy firefighter in "Backdraft." 
</P>
<P>
 Most recently seen: In the altogether with Sherilyn Fenn and Kelly Lynch in 
"Three of Hearts" and with Sharon Stone in "Sliver." 
</P>
<P>
 Look: Eurotrash version of Alec: slightly watered down and callow; prettier 
but less rugged. Typical role: Romantic lead with much to learn -- about women 
and himself. Chest hair: Virile thatch, but not overrun like Alec. 
Extracurricular activities: Upholding the Baldwin bachelor tradition, so that 
his brothers might live through him vicariously. Career trajectory: Needs a 
role that casts him as something other than the roadshow Alec. * 
</P>
<P>
 Name: Stephen Age: 27 Significant other: Wife Kennya; married June, 1990. 
First made an impression: Slapping leather on "The Young Riders." Movie 
breakthrough role: As the white guy in Mario Van Peebles' "Posse." Most 
recently seen: In "8 Seconds" as a rodeo star and in upcoming "Threesome" as 
one-third of an unconventional roommate arrangement. Look: Like an Alec whose 
DNA has been scrambled. Typical role: The hero's slightly doofy buddy with a 
heart of gold; the boor with a secret streak of vulnerability. Chest hair: 
Hairless as a pre-adolescent. Extracurricular activities: Posing for beefcake 
calendar. Career trajectory: On the upswing, if he can grow into character 
roles once played by Warren Oates and Randy Quaid.; ; ; 
</P>
