<HEADLINE>
<P>
UC IRVINE BEATS SOUTH ALABAMA FOR TENNIS TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The UC Irvine men's tennis team defeated South Alabama, 4-3, to win the 15th 
annual UCI Tennis Classic Saturday at the UCI Tennis Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 Carlos Bustos, who did not play the past two days because of knee problems, 
defeated Kal Petersson, 5-7, 7-6, 6-2, to clinch the title. 
</P>
<P>
 Sophomore Julian Foxon won his 10th consecutive match, improving his 
dual-match record to 17-2. 
</P>
<P>
 The Anteaters, who won the title for the first time since 1988, improved to 
11-8. 
</P>
