SUNNY HILLS' KIM LOSES TO HIS DOUBLES PARTNER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kevin Kim, a sophomore at Sunny Hills High and top-seeded in the boys' 16 
division of the Easter Bowl Junior Tennis Championships, was defeated by his 
doubles partner, sixth-seeded Michael Russell, of Bloomfield Hills, Mich., 6-2, 
2-6, 6-2, in the final Saturday at Doral Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Kim reached the final by defeating Mike Bryan of Camarillo, 6-4, 7-6 (7-3), in 
a semifinal Friday. 
