<HEADLINE>
<P>
NO RADIOACTIVITY FOUND IN FRENCH REACTOR BLAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 French authorities said Friday they had found no radioactive contamination 
from an explosion at a disused nuclear reactor in southern France Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 The blast, in an experimental fast-breeder reactor being dismantled at 
Cadarache, killed one worker and injured four. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities did not evacuate the area around the sprawling nuclear complex, at 
Cadarache, 45 miles northwest of Marseilles. The reactor was halted 11 years 
ago. 
</P>
