<HEADLINE>
<P>
VILLAGE 1-WOMAN POLICE DEPARTMENT SHUTS DOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The police department has disbanded, and Carol Goff is out of a job. 
</P>
<P>
 Village officials surveyed Martin's 462 residents earlier this year, asking if 
they were willing to pay higher property taxes to cover the $29,000-a-year 
expense for the one-woman department. 
</P>
<P>
 About 60% said no. So the department officially disbanded Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's really hard -- law enforcement is in my blood," said Goff, who was the 
entire village police force for more than 10 years. 
</P>
<P>
 Goff, a 38-year-old single mother of three children, will keep working 
part-time with the police department in nearby Allegan. 
</P>
