<HEADLINE>
<P>
LAGUNA NEEDS POLICE EXPLORER PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * We are all aware that our Laguna Beach Police Department is understaffed. So 
I was particularly appalled to hear that (Councilman) Bob Gentry, with the 
support of (Councilwoman) Ann Christoph, has decided to try to get rid of the 
police Explorer program in Laguna Beach at the City Council meeting Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The police Explorers is a program in which young people, up to age 21, assist 
our Police Department providing volunteer service to help keep our city safe. 
They helped evacuate Laguna during the fire. They learn firsthand about public 
safety, public administration and what it takes to keep our streets safe. 
</P>
<P>
 This program is good for Laguna Beach and for the young people in our 
community who volunteer an incredible number of hours of service. 
</P>
<P>
 However, Gentry and Christoph have a problem with this because the police 
Explorers are associated with the Boy Scouts of America, and the Boy Scouts of 
America are opposed to having gay troop leaders in charge of young and 
impressionable Scouts. I'd say Gentry is obviously trying to impose his 
personal preference on the citizens of Laguna Beach again, and at the expense 
of our public safety. 
</P>
<P>
 Call your council representative and let him or her know what you think about 
this issue. 
</P>
<P>
 Better yet, attend the council meeting on Tuesday and support the police 
Explorer program. 
</P>
<P>
 STEVE BRIDGES 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach 
</P>
