<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHOT IN DRUG BUY, DYING MAN TELLS POLICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 26-year-old man was shot and killed late Friday, apparently after a drug 
deal that went awry, police said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, Ernesto Rivera Perez, stumbled out of an apartment in the 1400 
block of North Broadway about 10:30 p.m. Friday and collapsed in the street, 
where he was discovered a short time later by a Santa Ana police officer on 
patrol.He was taken to UCI Medical Center in Orange, where he died during 
surgery, Faust said. 
</P>
<P>
 Before he died, Perez, who was shot in the chest and abdomen, told police he 
was buying marijuana when he was attacked, said Sgt. Dick Faust. 
</P>
<P>
 "He said he was shot by three guys with masks, but that's doubtful," Faust 
said. "A female witness said she saw a male running from the area with a 
handgun and he wasn't wearing a mask." 
</P>
<P>
 Police said they have made no arrests and have no suspects in the case. 
</P>
</TEXT>
