<P>
WOMAN TIED UP BUT UNINJURED IN HOME INVASION ROBBERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three teens forced their way into the home of an 85-year-old woman Saturday 
morning and then tied her up before stealing belongings valued at more than 
$850. 
</P>
<P>
 Police released few details about the robbery, which they said happened about 
9:30 a.m. at a home on Coralwood Lane. 
</P>
<P>
 The elderly woman, who was uninjured, was later freed by a family member. 
Authorities said they have no suspects in the robbery. 
</P>
