COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTHWEST: JEFFERSON PARK; REFURBISHED LIBRARY OPENS ITS DOORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Jefferson Vassie D. Wright Memorial Branch Library opened its expanded 
facility last week at 3311 W. Jefferson Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 The opening was marked by a ribbon-cutting ceremony, used book sale and 
daylong musical celebration in nearby Shaw Park. Improvements, which took about 
eight months to complete, included a new foyer, carpet, paint and installation 
of public restrooms -- the first for the library since opening in 1923. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was a long time in coming, but we're really happy about this," said senior 
librarian Gladys Cole. "This is the only library in the Jefferson Park area. . 
. . It's important to the community as a resource, particularly for kids." 
