<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRINCE EDWARD TO WED, PAPER SAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Queen Elizabeth II's youngest son, Prince Edward, will marry his girlfriend, 
Sophie Rhys-Jones, in a low-key ceremony this summer, the Sunday Express 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
 The newspaper quoted palace sources as saying preparations were well advanced 
for a wedding in late July or early August. 
</P>
<P>
 "It will be a low-key wedding and will take place before the first leaves 
fall," the Sunday Express quoted an unnamed peer with close connections to the 
Royal Family as saying. 
</P>
<P>
 On Saturday, the couple were reported on their way to Windsor Castle, west of 
London, where the Queen and family traditionally spend several weeks at Easter. 
</P>
<P>
 Edward, 30, is the Queen's only unmarried child. The other three -- heir 
Prince Charles, Princess Anne and Prince Andrew -- have had troubled marriages. 
</P>
