<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; FREEWAY CRASH INJURES AGOURA WOMAN, 23 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A traffic accident early Saturday morning in Thousand Oaks left an Agoura 
woman seriously injured, California Highway Patrol officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Heather Dawn Sandy, 23, was driving south on the Ventura Freeway near 
Hampshire Road shortly after 4 a.m. when she veered, struck the center divider. 
Her vehicle overturned several times, officials said.  
</P>
<P>
 She suffered major head injuries and was taken to Westlake Hospital, where she 
underwent surgery, a nursing supervisor said. Sandy was listed in stable 
condition in the intensive care unit Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Sandy's passenger, Carrie Mcauliffe, 26, of Oxnard, suffered minor injuries 
and refused medical treatment, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The CHP briefly closed a portion of the southbound Ventura Freeway at 
Hampshire Road after the accident. TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
