<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; COMPUTER PARTS DESTROYED IN FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A computer-repair business in Simi Valley suffered about $110,000 damage in a 
two-alarm fire that swept through a large industrial building, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The fire at Independent Technology, 310 E. Easy St., was reported just after 
11 p.m. Thursday and was extinguished by firefighters about 30 minutes later. 
</P>
<P>
 The blaze caused an estimated $10,000 worth of damage to the 
15,000-square-foot warehouse and destroyed $100,000 worth of computer parts, 
County Fire Investigator Peter Cronk said. 
</P>
<P>
 A cause has not been determined, but Cronk said it started inside a stockroom. 
</P>
<P>
 Fire Capt. Keith Mashburn said fire crews had a tough time locating the fire 
because the smoke inside the warehouse was so dense. To vent the building, 
firefighters cut holes in the roof. 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Prinkey, the company's operations director, said the fire and smoke 
damage is covered by insurance. JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</TEXT>
