<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL / DAILY REPORT; WOMEN'S FINAL FOUR; FOR ALABAMA, IT WAS THE 
CRUELEST CUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Alabama seemed to lose its momentum when Niesa Johnson, the team's floor 
leader, cut her right hand hitting a faucet in the locker room at 
halftime.Seven stitches were needed to close the cut and she missed the first 4 
1/2 minutes of the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 "Right at the start of the second half, I couldn't feel my fingers, but it 
started coming along fairly quickly," Johnson said. "I would not have played in 
a normal situation." 
</P>
