<HEADLINE>
<P>
GLENDORA REALTOR NAMED TOP SELLER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Glendora real estate agent Marty Rodriguez was named top seller in the world 
by Century 21 Real Estate Corp. for an unprecedented third year in a row. She 
was also No. 1 in North America for the fifth straight year. 
</P>
<P>
 Rodriguez sold 173 houses worth more than $40 million in 1993 and earned more 
than $1.22 million in gross closed commissions. 
</P>
<P>
 "We are delighted to be No. 1 in the world and North America again in 1993," 
said Rodriguez, who has a staff of eight. "It's nice to see the hours of work 
and late nights pay off." 
</P>
<P>
 Rodriguez, who works with Century 21 Alosta in Glendora, has been selling real 
estate in the east San Gabriel Valley for more than 15 years. 
</P>
